    'guestmedia' =>
q~¿Evitar que los visitantes puedan ver ficheros multimedia y enlaces publicados en los mensajes?~,
    'guestlang' => q~¿Permitir que los visitantes elijan idioma?~,
    'checkspace' =>
q~Enabling this will allow you to set the various free disk space checks. Checking the free disk space is primarily a Linux function and may not work properly on Windows/IIS servers. The free disk space functions may return incorrect values when used on shared hosting services.~,
    'checkspace2' =>
q~ (If the Free Disk Space Functions Utility page fails to load your server <b>does not support those functions</b>.)~,
    'checkspclabel' => q~Advanced Settings - Free Disk Space Functions~,
    'quota' =>
q~<i>quota</i>: Habilitando esta opción se usa el Shell de Linux \'quota\' para comprobar el espacio libre de host.Este es el método preferido. La casilla será inhabilitada si esta opción no está disponible en tu servidor.<br /><span class="small">Si tu espacio en disco disponible baja de los 100&thinsp;000 Bytes (100 KB), el foro se pondrá automáticamente en mantenimiento para prevenir la pérdida de datos.<br />Recuerda: Sólo los Administradores puede acceder al foro cuanto está en modo Mantenimiento.</span>~,
    'quota_value' =>
q~<i>quota</i>: Selecciona el Fichero de Sistema tu foro está activo:<br /><span class="small">El Fichero de Sistema correcto debe ser preseleccionado si \'quota\' fue grabado <i>disabled</i> antes.</span>~,
    'quotahostuser' =>
q~<i>quota</i>: Tu nombre de usuario en tu servidor:<br /><span class="small">Debe ser preescrito. Disponible si la casilla anterior está seleccionada.</span>~,
    'findtime' =>
q~<i>find</i>: Tiempo entre que el Linux Shell \'find\' comprueba el tamaño de los ficheros en el directorio que debes insertar más abajo y sus subdirectorios. Este y los dos siguientes campos serán desactivados si este comando no está disponible en tu servidor.<br />Dejar en 0 si se quiere elegir otro método de comprobación como \'quota\' o chequeo de espacio libre en disco.<br /><span class="small">Como esto puede ser un trabajo que lleve mucho tiempo, debes insertar un valor razonablemente alto como 300 (cinco horas) o 1440 (un día). Una vez el espacio libre en disco se ha obtenido después de cada \'find\', este método es de muy baja carga del servidor.</span>~,
    'findroot' =>
q~<i>find</i>: Ruta hacia el directorio raíz de tu cuenta de usuario en un sistema de hospedaje de usuario múltiple.<br /><span class="small">la ruta debe ser <b>desde la raíz del sistema hasta la raíz de tu usuario.</b>. Ejemplo:<br />/var/www/your_domain_name/<br />/var/www/web1234/<br /><br />También puedes especificar una ruta hasta tu foro o un directorio en tu foro y especificar el tamaño máximo para su límite. \'find\' usará ese límite en lugar de los límites de tu hospedaje. Example:<br />/var/www/your_domain_name/cgi-bin/yabb2/<br />/var/www/your_domain_name/public_html/yabbfiles/Attachments/</span>~,
    'findmax' =>
q~<i>find</i>: Espacio disponible que estás autorizado a utilizar en el directorio de arriba (en Megabytes).<br /><span class="small">Debe ser la misma capacidad de disco This should be the same amount of disk space as your hosting plan advertises.<br />Since you should set \'find\' to check the available host space only all X hours or once per day, you should set this value lower than the space your host provides to you, to avoid running out of space due to some sudden increase of disk use for example by attachments or other high volume consuming postings.<br />To enable \'find\' for free host space checking this value must be &gt; 0. If the used space within the above directory is higher than this value, the forum will automatically go into Maintenance Mode to prevent running out of space and losing data.<br />Reminders:<br />Only Admins can access the forum when in Maintenance Mode.<br />Just in case you don\'t remember: 1 GB = 1024 MB</span>~,
    'diskspacecheck' => q~¿Habilitar comprobación de espacio libre en disco?~,
    'getreversedns'  => q~Enable Reverse DNS Lookup.~,
    'minlinkpost' =>
q~Número de mensajes que debe tener un miembro antes de poder publicar links e imágenes~,
    'minlinkpost_exp' =>
q~Esta acción impide que los spambots publiquen mensajes inmediatamente después de registrarse~,
    'minlinksig' =>
q~Number of posts a member must have before links and images can be created in signature~,
    'minlinksig_exp' =>
q~This avoids spambots from creating spam-signatures directly after registering~,
    'minlinkweb' =>
q~Number of posts a member must have before they can link to a website in their profile~,
    'minlinkweb_exp' =>
q~This prevents spammers from linking to a website directly after registering~,
    'stealth' =>
q~Habilitar modo \'Stealth\' para FA/Gmods:<br /><span class="small">Permite que el estado aparezca como OFFLINE/AUSENTE para todos los miembros que estén mirando</span>~,
    'mlview' => q~¿A quién le está permitido navegar por la lista de miembros?~,
    'buddylist' => q~Activar Lista de Amigos?~,
    'regreason' =>
      q~Número máximo de caracteres en el motivo de usuario para el Registro~,
    'showall' =>
      q~Mostrar "Todo" en los selectores de página y el sumario de los temas?~,
    'imageinquote' =>
q~Habilitar si quieres que las imágenes de un post aparezcan entre comillas en ese post.<br /><span class="small">Si no se habilita, las imágenes entre comillas se mostrarán como un link a la imagen.</span>~,
    'extendedprofiles' =>
q~¿Usar Perfiles Extendidos?<br /><span class="small">Si se habilita aparecerá en la parte izquierda una función adicional llamada "Campos de Perfil". Ahí podrás añadir funciones a los perfiles de los usuarios.<br />!Deja esta opción en blanco si quieres ahorrarle carga al servidor!</span>~,
    'forumnumbformat' => q~Select default number format:~,
    'nospammer' =>
q~Send default e-mail to rejected users even when no reason is given when registration is by Admin approval. Check for &#39;yes&#39;~,
    'honeypot' =>
q~Activate Honeypot Spambot catcher. Check for &#39;yes&#39; (<a href="{yabb adminurl}?action=honeypot">Edit Honeypot</a>)~,
    'spamfruits' =>
      q~Activate SpamFruits Spambot catcher. Check for &#39;yes&#39;~,
    'eventcal_set'  => q~Event Calendar Settings~,
    'eventcal_set1' => q~Edit your Event Calendar Settings~,
    'calsplit' =>
q~Maximum number of birthdays shown on page.<br /><span class="small">Page will split into individual month displays. Leave blank or set to 0 to disable.</span>~,
    'addtab_on' => q~Show Add and Edit Tabs on Forum?~,
    'rules'     => q~Board Rules~,
    'rules1'    => q~Enable Board Rules~,
    'rules2'    => q~Rules Title~,
    'rules3'    => q~Rules~,
    'rules4'    => q~You can use HTML here.~,
    'iplookup' =>
q~Enable IP Lookup?<br /><span class="small">Checking this option will turn IP Addresses into active links allowing you to look them up on a Whois server.</span>~,
    'iplookup_urls' =>
q~IP Lookup Whois Servers:<br /><span class="small">Here you can add or remove Whois servers to/from the IP Lookup page.<br />Use {ip} in the URL to substitute the actual IP address, and separate the title and URL with a pipe symbol \'|\'.<br />One URL per line.<br />Example: MyLookupSite|mylookupsite.com?ip={ip}</span>~,
    'iplookup_protocols' => q~. Valid protocols are http and https.~,
    'show_user_age'      => q~Show User Age in Message View?~,
    'show_reg_date'      => q~Show User Registration Date in Message View?~,
    'edit_gender_limit' =>
q~Set a limit on the amount of times that members can edit their gender:<br /><span class="small">1 = Cannot be edited after the first time it has been entered.<br />0 = No limit.</span>~,
    'edit_age_limit' =>
q~Set a limit on the amount of times that members can edit their birthdate:<br /><span class="small">1 = Cannot be edited after the first time it has been entered.<br />0 = No limit.</span>~,
    'min_reg_time' =>
q~Minimum amount of time in seconds which must be spent on the registration page:<br /><span class="small">This is to stop spambots which automatically fill in the registration form in a time which is humanly impossible.<br />Set to 0 to disable.</span>~,
    'ipblock'         => q~Block IP in Guardian~,
    'ipblock2'        => q~Block IP in .htaccess~,
    'ipblock_confirm' => q~Are you sure you want to block this IP?\n\n~,
    'ipban_confirm'   => q~Are you sure you want to ban this IP?\n\n~,
    'userpicml'       => q~Show User Avatar in Member List?~,
    'group_stars_ml'  => q~Show Group Stars in Member List?~,
    'default_avatar' =>
      q~Show a default avatar if the member has not added a picture?~,
    'default_userpic' =>
q~Default avatar image:<br /><span class="small">Allowed file types: png jpg jpeg gif<br />Max. file size: 250KB</span>~,
    'edit'   => q~Edit~,
    'delete' => q~Delete~,
    'cancel' => q~Cancel~,
    'enable_guest_view_limit' =>
q~Enable Guest Topic View Limit?<br /><span class="small">Checking this option will set a cookie to limit the amount of topics that guests can view before they are encouraged to register. You can set the amount of topic views and how you want it to behave below.</span>~,
    'guest_view_limit' =>
q~Guest Topic View Limit:<br /><span class="small">Set the amount of topics that guests can view before they are encouraged to register.</span>~,
    'guest_view_limit_block' =>
q~Block Guests from viewing topics after they have reached the topic view limit?<br /><span class="small">Checking this option will block guests from viewing any more topics after the topic view limit has been reached.<br />Leaving unchecked will display a friendly message at the top of the message view.</span>~,
    'topichover'   => q~Enable Topic Hover on Message Index~,
    'staff_reason' => q~Enable 'Reason for Editing' for Staff Members~,
    'user_reason'  => q~Enable 'Reason for Editing' for Members~,
    'brdrss1'      => q~RSS~,
    'brdrss2' =>
q~Check to show RSS Feed for this category on the Board Index.<br /><b>Note:</b> Only relevant if RSS is enabled.~,
    'brdrss3' =>
q~Check to show RSS Feed for this board on the Board Index.<br /><b>Note:</b> Only relevant if RSS is enabled and the board is not an external link board.~,
    'actions'      => q~Actions~,
    'remove_file'  => q~Remove File~,
    'current_img'  => q~Current Image~,
    'remove_img'   => q~Remove Image~,
    'for_template' => q~For template~,
    'setsettings'  => q~Settings Submitted~,
    'maxadminlog'  => q~The maximum number of entries stored in the Admin Log.~,
    'imp_email_check' =>
q~Enable improved e-mail checking?<br /><span class="small">Checks if the e-mail domain exists, if the user is known on the given SMTP server, if the smtp server(s) are online and valid, and if the users mailbox is full. Also adds a second e-mail field to the registration page for verification.<br />Note that this setting requires Net::DNS to be installed on your server.</span>~,
    'zodiac' => q~Show Zodiac Signs in Profile displays?~,
    'no_imp_email_check' =>
q~<br /><span class="important">Improved email check not available. Needs Net::DNS</span>~,
    'error_spd' =>
q~ErrorLog speed banning. Minimum number of seconds between multiple error log entries from the same IP address. <br /><span class="small">Violators are banned through .htaccess if allowed. Set to '0' to disable</span>~,
    'profile_int' =>
q~Redirect guest clicks on member name links to a 'Register or Login' page. Uncheck to disable member name links for guests.~,
    'ban_res' =>
q~You may add a short reason for the ban by using a '|' symbol to separate the IP address, e-mail address, or user ID and the reason for banning.~,
    'p_ban'     => q~Permanent~,
    'expired'   => q~Expired~,
    'expireon'  => q~Expires on~,
    'close_box' => q~Close~,
    'dupbrd' =>
      q~<span class="important">Warning: There are duplicate Boards: </span>~,
    'dupbrdlnk' =>
q~<span class="important"><a href="{yabb adminurl}?action=fixboarddupes">Fix duplicate boards</a></span>~,
    'fixdupbrd' => q~Fix Duplicates~,
    'fixduprem' => q~Duplicate Boards removed~,
    'subbrd'    => q~Sub-Board~,
    'inbrd'     => q~in Board~,
    'incat'     => q~in Category~,
    'fixinstruct' =>
q~Select the <strong>incorrect</strong> board(s). You may need to reorganize the position of boards in their categories/boards when finished.<br /><span class="important">Be very careful with your selections to make sure you do not remove the copy of the board you want to keep.</span>~,
    'usercp' => q~USER's CP~,
    'ppostperms' =>
q~Print Post Permissions<br /><span class="small">Disable Print Post or set it to "All Members" if you have spambot problems with this function.</span>~,
    'ptopicperms' =>
q~Print Thread Permissions<br /><span class="small">Disable Print Thread or set it to "All Members" if you have spambot problems with this function.</span>~,
    '813a' =>
q~Enable Style Switcher Dropdown Field?<br /><span class="small">If enabled, selected groups have the have the option to quickly select and change the forum layout, assuming other templates or css stylesheets are available.</span>~,
